title: Doctor Who - The Tenth Planet
description:
DVD rip of the final first doctor story with final episode being animated. 

The Tenth Planet is the partly missing second serial of the fourth season in the British science fiction television series Doctor Who, which was first broadcast in four weekly parts from 8 to 29 October 1966. It was William Hartnell's last regular appearance as the First Doctor, and the first story to feature the Cybermen. Patrick Troughton also makes his first, uncredited appearance as the Second Doctor. Only three of the four episodes are held in the BBC archives; one remains missing, though this was recreated using animation for the DVD release of the story in 2013.
